verses.text: And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* said unto Noah , Come thou and all thy house into the ark ; for thee have I seen righteous before me in this generation.

Of every clean beast thou shalt take to thee by sevens , the male and his female : and of beasts that \add are\add* not clean by two , the male and his female.\f + \fr 7.2 \ft by sevens: Heb. seven seven\f*
Of fowls also of the air by sevens , the male and the female ; to keep seed alive upon the face of all the earth.\f + \fr 7.3 \ft by sevens: Heb. seven seven\f*

For yet seven days , and I will cause it to rain upon the earth forty days and forty nights ; and every living substance that I have made will I destroy from off the face of the earth.\f + \fr 7.4 \ft destroy: Heb. blot out\f* \p
And Noah did according unto all that the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* commanded him.
And Noah \add was\add* six hundred years old when the flood of waters was upon the earth. \p
¶ And Noah went in , and his sons , and his wife , and his sons’ wives with him, into the ark , because of the waters of the flood.
Of clean beasts , and of beasts that \add are\add* not clean , and of fowls , and of every thing that creepeth upon the earth ,
There went in two and two unto Noah into the ark , the male and the female , as God had commanded Noah.
And it came to pass after seven days , that the waters of the flood were upon the earth.\f + \fr 7.10 \ft after…: or, on the seventh day\f* \p

¶ In the six hundredth year of Noah’s life , in the second month , the seventeenth day of the month , the same day were all the fountains of the great deep broken up , and the windows of heaven were opened.\f + \fr 7.11 \ft windows: or, floodgates\f*
And the rain was upon the earth forty days and forty nights. \p
In the selfsame day entered Noah , and Shem , and Ham , and Japheth , the sons of Noah , and Noah’s wife , and the three wives of his sons with them, into the ark ;

They , and every beast after his kind , and all the cattle after their kind , and every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth after his kind , and every fowl after his kind , every bird of every sort.\f + \fr 7.14 \ft sort: Heb. wing\f*
And they went in unto Noah into the ark , two and two of all flesh , wherein \add is\add* the breath of life.
And they that went in , went in male and female of all flesh , as God had commanded him: and the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* shut him in. \p
And the flood was forty days upon the earth ; and the waters increased , and bare up the ark , and it was lift up above the earth.
And the waters prevailed , and were increased greatly upon the earth ; and the ark went upon the face of the waters.
And the waters prevailed exceedingly upon the earth ; and all the high hills , that \add were\add* under the whole heaven , were covered.
Fifteen cubits upward did the waters prevail ; and the mountains were covered. \p
And all flesh died that moved upon the earth , both of fowl , and of cattle , and of beast , and of every creeping thing that creepeth upon the earth , and every man :
All in whose nostrils \add was\add* the breath of life , of all that \add was\add* in the dry \add land\add*, died.\f + \fr 7.22 \ft the breath…: Heb. the breath of the spirit of life\f*

And every living substance was destroyed which was upon the face of the ground , both man , and cattle , and the creeping things , and the fowl of the heaven ; and they were destroyed from the earth : and Noah only remained \add alive\add*, and they that \add were\add* with him in the ark.
And the waters prevailed upon the earth an hundred and fifty days.
